initial directors.)  Lehman Brothers Holdings Inc. (LEHMQ) , which
has said it aims to win approval for a $65 billion liquidation
plan next month, named a committee to choose initial directors
to oversee the process. The panel will include representatives
from  Goldman Sachs Group Inc. (GS) , Fir Tree Partners and Mizuho
Corporate Bank Ltd., according to a court filing. Liquidators of
Lehman affiliates and the defunct firmâ€™s head of international
